Here are 5 ways one can mistakenly catch the deadly coronavirus in Nigeria, as the cases of the deadly virus continues to rise in the country. As at the time of filing this report, there are 1728 confirmed cases of coronavirus in Nigeria, with 196 confirmed yesterday. The federal government has revealed plans to reopen the economy gradually, as the total lockdown in Lagos, Ogun, and Abuja is set to be eased. As we all know, the virus that causes COVID-19 is mainly transmitted through droplets generated when an infected person coughs, sneezes, or exhales. These droplets are too heavy to hang in the air and quickly fall on floors or surfaces. In this post, we are going to be giving you the 5 ways you can mistakenly get the coronavirus in Nigeria;